data.current_summary: Allows new products from the seller to be loaded into the marketplace
data.current_description: This enpoint to creates new products in the Marketplace using `skuSellerId` as a primary key. This enpoint expects a json document with array of products. The server will load each product as an individual item that can be manipulated using your own `skuSellerId`. All requests to This endpoint are idenpontent with respect of the `skuSellerId`, this means that once a `skuSellerId` is created it cannot be re-created using this tool. In order to update use the PUT method with the correct `skuSellerId`. You can also use the POST /product to create a single product per request
data.summary_suggestion: Bulk load new products into the Marketplace
data.description_suggestion: Creates new products in the BrandLovers Marketplace in bulk. Accepts a JSON array of product objects, each identified by a unique skuSellerId. The server processes each product individually and loads them as separate items that can be independently managed. This operation is idempotent with respect to skuSellerId - duplicate skuSellerId values will not be re-created. To update existing products, use PUT methods with the corresponding skuSellerId. Requires authentication. Returns confirmation of successfully created products and any errors encountered. For single product creation, use POST /product instead.

data.summary_suggestion: Bulk update prices for multiple products
data.description_suggestion: Updates prices for multiple products in bulk. Accepts a JSON array of product objects, each containing skuSellerId and new price information. The server processes each price update individually and acknowledges as many updates as possible, even if some fail. Partial success is supported - failed updates will be reported while successful ones are applied. Requires authentication. Returns confirmation of successful price updates and any errors encountered. Prices take effect immediately. Use GET /products/status to verify final product status after bulk updates.

data.current_summary: Update product details
data.current_description: Update a single product information such as name, brand, attribute, dimension, etc. Please note that data from your request will be merged with existing data. This allows you to easliy update only certain fields without the need to re-inform the other unchanged fields. For example in order to update just the field `title` simply send just this field with new information, remaining fields will not be changed. In order to erase an item the field must be informed as its default value, for example in order to erase the `videos` field must be sent as videos:[]. The `skuSellerId` field is always mandatory in the path and in the product json Object.
data.summary_suggestion: Update product information with partial field support
data.description_suggestion: Updates a single product's information identified by `skuSellerId`. Supports partial updates - only provided fields are modified while existing data is preserved. For example, send only {"title": "new title"} to update just the title. To clear a field, send it with its default value (e.g., "videos": []). The `skuSellerId` is required in both the URL path and request body. Returns the updated product object. Supports updates to name, brand, attributes, dimensions, pricing, inventory, and other product fields.
